China Stocks: Gezhouba, Shenma, TCL, Xinjiang Goldwind

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-24T07:40:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/beiqi-foton-china-fiber-glass-csr-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 7.5 points, or 0.3 percent, to
2,767.06. The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  added 0.1 percent to 3,026.22.  Water companies: Chongqing Three Gorges Water Conservancy &
Electric Power Co. (600116 CH) surged 10 percent to 19.70 yuan,
the highest close since March 29. China Gezhouba Group Co.
(600068 CH) advanced 2.4 percent to 11.46 yuan, the highest
since May 10. China will increase investment in water
conservation projects this decade to 4 trillion yuan from 1.06
trillion yuan in the previous 10 years, Xinhua News Agency
reported yesterday, citing Minister of Water Resources Chen Lei.  Shenma Industry Co. (600810 CH), a fabrics and fiber maker,
surged by the 10 percent daily limit to 13.18 yuan. The company
will issue about 112 million additional shares at 12.04 yuan
each to its parent in exchange for stakes in four affiliates
valued at 1.35 billion yuan, according to a statement to the
 Shanghai Stock Exchange  today.  TCL Corp. (000100)  (000100 CH), China’s largest consumer electronics
maker by market value, lost 4.3 percent to 2.88 yuan, its lowest
close since April 29. The company said shareholder Li Dongsheng
plans to sell no more than 40 million shares in the company in
the next three months to repay a 100 million yuan loan used to
participate in TCL’s private share placement last year.  Xinjiang Goldwind Science & Technology Co. (002202 CH) sank
1.5 percent to 15.79 yuan, its lowest close since July 5. The
company plans to subscribe for as much as $15 million worth of
shares in China Huaneng Group Corp.’s wind unit through its
initial public offering in  Hong Kong , according to a statement
to the Shenzhen Stock Exchange yesterday.  Zibo Wanchang Science & Technology Co. (002581 CH)
retreated 6.8 percent to 21.93 yuan. The company said its
Chairman Gao Qingchang died yesterday, without saying how,
according to a statement to Shenzhen’s stock exchange today.  --Irene Shen, Dingmin Zhang. Editor: Reinie Booysen  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
